    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-10-25T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-10-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="616"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d616">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">Julian Pauncefote</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Olney</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">British Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-10-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 25, 1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge, with thanks, the
                    receipt of Mr. Uhl’s note, No. 228, of the 22d instant, in which he informs me
                    that the commanding officer of the revenue steamer <hi rend="italic">Corwin</hi>
                    has been directed to proceed, with his command, to Victoria, British Columbia,
                    and report to Rear-Admiral Stephenson or the senior naval officer at that
                    station, for the purpose of giving testimony in regard to the trial of the
                    British sealing schooner <hi rend="italic">Shelby.</hi>
                </p>
                <pb facs="0740" n="680" xml:id="pg_680"/>
                <p>I have taken steps to obtain early information as to the date which will be fixed
                    upon for the trial of the <hi rend="italic">Beatrice</hi>, and I will not fail
                    to communicate further with you in regard to this subject.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Julian Pauncefote</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
